##### PARTICLE SPECTRA                                            2043 1451
                                                                  2043 1451
For Ca-46, an adjustment of the default matrix element            2043 1451
parameterization of [kon04b] for pre-equilibrium reactions of a   2043 1451
factor of 0.7 was needed, to describe the emission spectra for    2043 1451
nuclides in this mass range.                                      2043 1451
For high-energy neutron and charged particle spectra, the average 2043 1451
quality is also determined by the pre-equilibrium model and its   2043 1451
global parameterization. No high-energy experiments are           2043 1451
available, though neutron induced reaction spectra between 28 and 2043 1451
63 MeV on Al [ben02], Si [ben02b] and Fe [sly03] have enabled us  2043 1451
to better constrain the results, through the aforementioned       2043 1451
matrix element, for particle yields and double-differential       2043 1451
spectra for all ejectiles up to alpha particles.                  2043 1451
